Title: Crop area estimation by data-driven decomposition of mixed pixels in Landsat-TM images  
Author: M. S. KLEIN GEBBINCK and T. E. SCHOUTEN 
Address: Nijmegen, Toernooiveld 1, 6525 ED Nijmegen, the Netherlands  
Affiliation: Computing Science Institute, Faculty of Mathematics and Informatics, University of  
Abstract: Pixel-based classification is a standard approach towards crop area estimation, but it is unsuited to handle mixed pixels. Therefore, we developed the data-driven decomposition method, which combines the linear mixture model with knowledge of the application domain. A quantitative comparison proved that both concepts lead to more accurate estimates when processing simulated images. Experiments on a real Landsat-TM image showed that our method estimated the area of 13 out of 17 lots more accurately than a similar approach based on classification. These results suggest that data-driven decomposition is a more accurate method to estimate the area of an agricultural field.
